   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# News Topic Classification\\n\",\"\\n\",\"**NLP Project 5 of 100**\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"\\n\",\"This notebook builds a text classifier that categorizes news articles into topics such as **politics, sports, technology, business, and entertainment**. We compare a TF-IDF + Logistic Regression baseline against a fine-tuned transformer (ModernBERT / DistilBERT) and evaluate with multi-class classification metrics.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"\\n\",\"1. Load and explore a multi-class news dataset (AG News or 20 Newsgroups).\\n\",\"2. Build a strong TF-IDF + LogisticRegression baseline.\\n\",\"3. Fine-tune a transformer-based classifier with Hugging Face.\\n\",\"4. Evaluate with accuracy, macro-F1, per-class precision/recall, and confusion matrix.\\n\",\"5. Understand the trade-offs between classic and deep-learning NLP classifiers.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Problem Statement\\n\",\"\\n\",\"Given a short news article or headline, predict which topic category it belongs to. This is a **multi-class classification** task.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Why This Project Matters\\n\",\"\\n\",\"- News organizations use topic classifiers for content routing and recommendation.\\n\",\"- Search engines categorize articles for better retrieval.\\n\",\"- Analysts track topic volumes to detect trends.\\n\",\"- It's a classic multi-class NLP problem that teaches core skills.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\"\\n\",\"We use the **AG News** dataset (4 classes: World, Sports, Business, Sci/Tech) with 120,000 training and 7,600 test samples.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"| Property | Value |\\n\",\"|----------|-------|\\n\",\"| Source | Hugging Face `fancyzhx/ag_news` |\\n\",\"| Classes | 4 (World, Sports, Business, Sci/Tech) |\\n\",\"| Size | ~127,600 total |\\n\",\"| License | Academic / research use |\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\"\\n\",\"AG News is a widely used academic benchmark. Available via Hugging Face Datasets.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Environment Setup\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scikit-learn\\\", \\\"datasets\\\", \\\"transformers\\\"]:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace(\\\"-\\\",\\\"_\\\"))\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\nprint(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Imports\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np\\nimport pandas as pd\\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\nimport seaborn as sns\\nimport warnings\\nwarnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\n\\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\nfrom sklearn.metrics import (accuracy_score, classification_report,\\n                             confusion_matrix, f1_score)\\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\nprint('Imports loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Configuration / Constants\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"SEED = 42\\nMAX_ROWS = 30000  # sample for speed\\nLABEL_NAMES = ['World', 'Sports', 'Business', 'Sci/Tech']\\nnp.random.seed(SEED)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset Download and Loading\\n\",\"\\n\",\"We load AG News from Hugging Face Datasets. This downloads automatically on first run and is cached afterwards.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"from datasets import load_dataset\\n\\nds = load_dataset('fancyzhx/ag_news')\\ntrain_df = ds['train'].to_pandas()\\ntest_df = ds['test'].to_pandas()\\n\\n# Sample for speed\\nif len(train_df) > MAX_ROWS:\\n    train_df = train_df.sample(n=MAX_ROWS, random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\n\\nprint(f'Train: {train_df.shape}, Test: {test_df.shape}')\\ntrain_df.head()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Data Validation Checks\\n\",\"\\n\",\"We verify the dataset has the expected columns, no missing values, and balanced classes.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"print(f'Columns: {list(train_df.columns)}')\\nprint(f'Missing values:\\\\n{train_df.isnull().sum()}')\\nprint(f'Duplicates: {train_df.duplicated().sum()}')\\nprint(f'\\\\nLabel distribution:')\\nprint(train_df['label'].value_counts().sort_index())\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Data Cleaning / Preprocessing\\n\",\"\\n\",\"AG News is relatively clean. We'll do minimal preprocessing: lowercase and strip whitespace. For the TF-IDF baseline we keep it simple — the vectorizer handles tokenization.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"train_df['clean_text'] = train_df['text'].str.lower().str.strip()\\ntest_df['clean_text'] = test_df['text'].str.lower().str.strip()\\n\\nprint(f'Sample cleaned text:\\\\n{train_df[\\\"clean_text\\\"].iloc[0][:200]}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Exploratory Data Analysis\\n\",\"\\n\",\"Let's look at class balance, text length distributions, and common words per class.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\\n# Class distribution\\ntrain_df['label'].map(lambda x: LABEL_NAMES[x]).value_counts().plot(\\n    kind='bar', ax=axes[0], color='steelblue', edgecolor='black')\\naxes[0].set_title('Class Distribution')\\naxes[0].set_ylabel('Count')\\n\\n# Text length\\ntrain_df['text_len'] = train_df['clean_text'].str.len()\\ntrain_df['text_len'].hist(bins=50, ax=axes[1], edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)\\naxes[1].set_title('Text Length Distribution')\\naxes[1].set_xlabel('Characters')\\n\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Task-Specific Preparation\\n\",\"\\n\",\"We prepare features (X) and labels (y) for both baseline and transformer approaches.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"X_train = train_df['clean_text'].values\\ny_train = train_df['label'].values\\nX_test = test_df['clean_text'].values\\ny_test = test_df['label'].values\\n\\nprint(f'X_train: {len(X_train)}, X_test: {len(X_test)}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Baseline Approach: TF-IDF + Logistic Regression\\n\",\"\\n\",\"This is a strong and fast baseline for text classification. TF-IDF captures word importance, and logistic regression handles multi-class well.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=30000, sublinear_tf=True, ngram_range=(1, 2))\\nX_train_tfidf = tfidf.fit_transform(X_train)\\nX_test_tfidf = tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n\\nlr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=SEED, C=1.0)\\nlr.fit(X_train_tfidf, y_train)\\n\\ny_pred_base = lr.predict(X_test_tfidf)\\nacc_base = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_base)\\nf1_base = f1_score(y_test, y_pred_base, average='macro')\\n\\nprint(f'=== Baseline: TF-IDF + LogisticRegression ===')\\nprint(f'Accuracy: {acc_base:.4f}')\\nprint(f'Macro F1: {f1_base:.4f}')\\nprint(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_base, target_names=LABEL_NAMES))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Main Model: Transformer Fine-Tuning\\n\",\"\\n\",\"We fine-tune a DistilBERT model on the AG News dataset for better performance. If GPU is available, training is much faster.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"**Note**: If running without GPU, this cell may take 10-20 minutes. You can skip it and rely on the baseline results.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import torch\\nfrom transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForSequenceClassification, Trainer, TrainingArguments\\nfrom datasets import Dataset\\n\\ndevice = 'cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu'\\nprint(f'Device: {device}')\\n\\nMODEL_NAME = 'distilbert-base-uncased'\\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME)\\n\\ndef tokenize_fn(examples):\\n    return tokenizer(examples['text'], truncation=True, padding='max_length', max_length=128)\\n\\n# Use smaller sample for transformer training\\ntrain_ds = Dataset.from_pandas(train_df[['text', 'label']].head(10000))\\ntest_ds = Dataset.from_pandas(test_df[['text', 'label']].head(2000))\\n\\ntrain_ds = train_ds.map(tokenize_fn, batched=True)\\ntest_ds = test_ds.map(tokenize_fn, batched=True)\\ntrain_ds.set_format('torch', columns=['input_ids', 'attention_mask', 'label'])\\ntest_ds.set_format('torch', columns=['input_ids', 'attention_mask', 'label'])\\n\\nmodel = AutoModelForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(MODEL_NAME, num_labels=4).to(device)\\n\\ntraining_args = TrainingArguments(\\n    output_dir='./results', num_train_epochs=2, per_device_train_batch_size=32,\\n    per_device_eval_batch_size=64, warmup_steps=100, weight_decay=0.01,\\n    logging_steps=50, eval_strategy='epoch', save_strategy='no',\\n    report_to='none', seed=SEED\\n)\\n\\ndef compute_metrics(eval_pred):\\n    preds = np.argmax(eval_pred.predictions, axis=1)\\n    acc = accuracy_score(eval_pred.label_ids, preds)\\n    f1 = f1_score(eval_pred.label_ids, preds, average='macro')\\n    return {'accuracy': acc, 'f1': f1}\\n\\ntrainer = Trainer(model=model, args=training_args, train_dataset=train_ds,\\n                  eval_dataset=test_ds, compute_metrics=compute_metrics)\\ntrainer.train()\\nresults = trainer.evaluate()\\nprint(f'\\\\nTransformer Results: {results}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Evaluation\\n\",\"\\n\",\"We compare baseline and transformer results side by side.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"print('=== Results Comparison ===')\\nprint(f'{\\\"Model\\\":<35} {\\\"Accuracy\\\":>10} {\\\"Macro F1\\\":>10}')\\nprint('-' * 55)\\nprint(f'{\\\"TF-IDF + LogisticRegression\\\":<35} {acc_base:>10.4f} {f1_base:>10.4f}')\\ntry:\\n    print(f'{\\\"DistilBERT Fine-tuned\\\":<35} {results[\\\"eval_accuracy\\\"]:>10.4f} {results[\\\"eval_f1\\\"]:>10.4f}')\\nexcept:\\n    print(f'{\\\"DistilBERT Fine-tuned\\\":<35} {\\\"(skipped)\\\":>10} {\\\"(skipped)\\\":>10}')\\n\\n# Confusion matrix for baseline\\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))\\ncm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_base)\\nsns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=LABEL_NAMES, yticklabels=LABEL_NAMES, ax=ax)\\nax.set_title('Confusion Matrix — Baseline')\\nax.set_xlabel('Predicted'); ax.set_ylabel('Actual')\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Error Analysis\\n\",\"\\n\",\"Let's examine misclassified examples to understand where the model struggles.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"errors = test_df.copy()\\nerrors['pred'] = y_pred_base\\nerrors['correct'] = errors['label'] == errors['pred']\\nwrong = errors[~errors['correct']].head(10)\\nfor _, row in wrong.iterrows():\\n    print(f'True: {LABEL_NAMES[row[\\\"label\\\"]]} | Pred: {LABEL_NAMES[row[\\\"pred\\\"]]}')\\n    print(f'  {row[\\\"text\\\"][:120]}...')\\n    print()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Interpretation / Insights\\n\",\"\\n\",\"1. **TF-IDF + LogReg achieves strong accuracy** (~91%) — a reminder that classical methods remain competitive for short text classification.\\n\",\"2. **Transformers provide a small uplift** (~93-94%) by capturing semantic context that bag-of-words misses.\\n\",\"3. **Sports and Sci/Tech are easiest** to classify due to distinctive vocabulary.\\n\",\"4. **Business vs World** is the most confused pair — they share geopolitical and economic language.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Limitations\\n\",\"\\n\",\"1. AG News is a benchmark dataset — real news classification involves more nuanced and overlapping categories.\\n\",\"2. Only 4 classes — production systems often need 10-30+ categories.\\n\",\"3. No temporal shift analysis — news topics evolve.\\n\",\"4. Short snippets — real articles are longer and may span multiple topics.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## How to Improve This Project\\n\",\"\\n\",\"1. Use ModernBERT or a larger transformer for higher accuracy.\\n\",\"2. Add more classes and train on a custom dataset.\\n\",\"3. Implement multi-label classification (articles can belong to multiple topics).\\n\",\"4. Add confidence calibration and threshold tuning.\\n\",\"5. Deploy as a REST API with batch inference.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Production Considerations\\n\",\"\\n\",\"- Latency: TF-IDF + LogReg is much faster than transformer inference.\\n\",\"- Model size: DistilBERT is ~250MB vs a few MB for TF-IDF + LogReg.\\n\",\"- Monitoring: Track class distribution drift over time.\\n\",\"- A/B testing: Compare models on live traffic before full rollout.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\"\\n\",\"1. Not lowercasing or normalizing text before TF-IDF.\\n\",\"2. Using accuracy alone on imbalanced datasets (here classes are balanced, so it's OK).\\n\",\"3. Fine-tuning too long and overfitting on small datasets.\\n\",\"4. Not comparing against a strong baseline before jumping to transformers.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\"\\n\",\"1. Try a different model (e.g., `roberta-base`) and compare.\\n\",\"2. Add a 5th class by combining with another dataset.\\n\",\"3. Implement a simple ensemble of TF-IDF + transformer predictions.\\n\",\"4. Plot learning curves to find the minimum training data needed.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\"\\n\",\"1. **News topic classification is a well-defined multi-class NLP problem.**\\n\",\"2. **TF-IDF + LogReg is a fast, strong baseline** that should always be tried first.\\n\",\"3. **Transformers provide modest gains** on clean, short-text classification tasks.\\n\",\"4. **Error analysis reveals systematic confusion** between semantically close categories.\\n\",\"5. **This pipeline generalizes** to any short-text multi-class classification task.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
